  "TOPAZ-THOUGHT-STR": {
   "name": "TOPAZ-THOUGHT-STR",
   "kind": "global",
   "file": "bad.zil",
   "line": 34,
   "value": "\"You consider telling Topaz who and what you are, but it is too\ndangerous; your own men are probably swarming the area, and any\ncontact with Topaz would blow your cover wide open.\""
  },
  "FESTIVITIES-SQ": {
   "name": "FESTIVITIES-SQ",
   "kind": "global",
   "file": "bad.zil",
   "line": 104,
   "value": "<PLTABLE <> <> <> <> <> <> <> <> <> <> <> <> \"The town's fifteenth century clock strikes the hour, indicating that the\nceremonies are shortly to commence.\" \"You watch as the mayor of Ostnitz comes to the podium at the front of the\ndais. He motions for the crowd to be silent for the playing of the national\nanthem.\" \"The anthem finished, the mayor calls upon the head of the church of\nLitzenburg to give a benediction.\" \"The priest departs, and the mayor announces the \"kickoff\" speaker,\nWilliam Henry Huttinger, the American ambassador. Amidst\nthe roaring approval of the crowd, Huttinger approaches the rostrum.|\n|\nIt may seem strange for an unaligned country to show such feeling for a\nformer member of the American military, but it was Huttinger\nwho led the Allied forces during the liberation of Litzenburg in 1945,\nand the people have not forgotten.|\n|\nHow ironic that the Kremlin chose this time, this place for the death\nof one of Litzenburg's only heroes. Even more ironic is that the irony is\nalmost certainly lost on them.\" \"Having calmed down the crowd, Huttinger begins to speak. The words seem\nto careen through your head but make little impact - there are only\nmoments now in which to act.\" \"\">"
  },
  "FESTIVITIES-F": {
   "name": "FESTIVITIES-F",
   "kind": "global",
   "file": "bad.zil",
   "line": 141,
   "value": "<PLTABLE <> <> <> <> <> <> <> <> <> <> <> <> \"The town's fifteenth century clock strikes the hour.\" \"You notice that the crowd has become quiet. After a moment, the national\nanthem begins to play.\" \"The anthem is now finished, and after a few moments, a benediction is\nread.\" \"The mayor announces the \"kickoff\" speaker, William Henry Huttinger, the\nAmerican ambassador. The crowd roars its approval; you've got only moments\nbefore it will be too late to save him!\" \"Huttinger begins to speak. The words seem to careen through your head but\nmake little impact - you have only moments in which to act.\" \"Huttinger continues to speak, and the crowd responds with enthusiasm,\ninterrupting him frequently.\">"
  },
  "FESTIVITIES": {
   "name": "FESTIVITIES",
   "kind": "global",
   "file": "bad.zil",
   "line": 167,
   "value": "<PLTABLE <> <> <> <> <> <> <> <> <> <> <> <> -1 \"The crowd noise subsides and the national anthem is begun.\" -1 -1 -1 -1>"
  },
